                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363 Manchuria/271: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-30T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 30, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>204. Your 249, December 21, 11 a.m., and previous. Department has informed New
                    York office of Standard-Vacuum that it is inclined to agree that, in view of
                    Ohashi’s letter to Ballantine, the company has exhausted its recourse to local
                    remedies and that, if the company believes that it has legal grounds for
                    diplomatic claim against the Japanese Government, Department is prepared, if
                    company so desires, to receive and consider such claim for possible future
                    action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
